  "prompt": "Bank Accounts: How do I know whether my bank account is linked to my Aadhaar card or not?",
  "response": "It's important to be aware that linking Aadhaar to bank accounts is **no longer mandatory** following a Supreme Court ruling. Banks might still ask for it for KYC purposes, but you are not legally obligated to provide it.\n\nHere are a few ways to check if your bank account *was* previously linked to your Aadhaar card, or if you simply want to confirm the KYC information your bank has on file:\n\n**1. Online Through UIDAI (Unique Identification Authority of India) Website:**\n\n*   **Visit the UIDAI Website:** Go to the official UIDAI website: [https://uidai.gov.in/](https://uidai.gov.in/)\n*   **Aadhaar Services:**  Look for the \"Aadhaar Services\" section.\n*   **Check Aadhaar Bank Linking Status:** You should find an option like \"Check Aadhaar/Bank Linking Status\" or a similarly worded option.\n*   **Enter Aadhaar Number:** You will need to enter your 12-digit Aadhaar number.\n*   **Enter Security Code:** Enter the security code (captcha) displayed on the screen.\n*   **OTP Authentication:**  An OTP (One-Time Password) will be sent to your registered mobile number (the mobile number registered with Aadhaar).\n*   **Enter OTP:** Enter the OTP received on your mobile number.\n*   **View Status:**  The website will then display the status of your Aadhaar-bank linking.  It will show the bank name and the date of linking (if linked).\n\n**Important Considerations for the UIDAI Method:**\n\n*   **Mobile Number Registration is Crucial:**  This method *only* works if your mobile number is registered with your Aadhaar.  If it isn't, you'll need to update it first (see below).\n*   **Privacy:** The UIDAI website shows only the *bank name* and the *date of linking*, but *not* the specific account number. This is for privacy reasons.\n*   **Potential Downtime:** The UIDAI website can sometimes experience high traffic, leading to slower response times or temporary unavailability.\n\n**2. Through Your Bank (Contacting Your Bank Directly):**\n\n*   **Visit Your Bank Branch:** The most reliable way is to visit your bank branch in person.\n    *   Speak to a bank representative.\n    *   Inquire about the status of your Aadhaar linking.\n    *   They can verify the information in their system.\n*   **Phone Banking/Customer Care:**  Call your bank's customer care number.\n    *   Follow the automated instructions or speak to a customer service representative.\n    *   Inquire about the Aadhaar linking status.  Be prepared to answer security questions to verify your identity.\n*   **Net Banking/Mobile Banking:**  Some banks provide this information within their net banking or mobile banking portals.\n    *   Log in to your online banking account.\n    *   Look for a section like \"Aadhaar Seeding,\" \"KYC Details,\" or \"Profile.\"\n    *   The Aadhaar linking status may be displayed there.\n\n**Important Considerations for the Bank Method:**\n\n*   **Identification:**  When visiting the bank in person, carry valid photo identification (Aadhaar card, PAN card, driver's license, etc.).\n*   **Security Questions:**  When contacting customer care, be prepared to answer security questions to verify your identity.\n*   **Varying Availability:**  The availability of this information online or via phone varies from bank to bank.\n\n**3. Using USSD Code (Limited Availability):**\n\n*   Some banks offer a USSD code to check the Aadhaar linking status. This is *not* a universal method.  You'll need to check if your specific bank offers this service.\n*   **How it Works (If Available):**  You dial a specific code from your registered mobile number (e.g., *99*99#).  Follow the on-screen instructions.\n*   **Check with Your Bank:**  Contact your bank to see if they provide a USSD code for this purpose.\n\n**What If My Mobile Number Isn't Registered with Aadhaar?**\n\n*   **Visit an Aadhaar Enrolment Center/Update Center:** You'll need to visit an authorized Aadhaar Enrolment Center or Update Center to register or update your mobile number with your Aadhaar.  You can find a nearby center using the UIDAI website's locator tool.  This requires biometric authentication.\n*   **Why It's Important:** A registered mobile number is essential for receiving OTPs for online Aadhaar-related services.\n\n**Important Notes and Disclaimers:**\n\n*   **No Legal Obligation to Link:** As stated earlier, linking Aadhaar to bank accounts is *not* mandatory as of the Supreme Court ruling.\n*   **KYC is Still Required:** Banks are still required to perform KYC (Know Your Customer) verification.  While they *may* request Aadhaar, you can provide other officially valid documents as proof of identity and address.\n*   **Privacy Concerns:** Be cautious about sharing your Aadhaar details with unknown or untrusted sources.\n*   **Official Sources:** Always rely on official sources like the UIDAI website and your bank's official website or customer service channels for accurate information.\n\nIn summary, the easiest and most reliable way to confirm if your bank account was linked to your Aadhaar is to contact your bank directly, either by visiting a branch or calling customer care. If you want to check online, the UIDAI website provides a service to check the linking status, but requires your mobile number to be registered with Aadhaar.  Remember that linking is no longer mandatory.\n",
